adjectives.description: multiform (comparative more multiform, superlative most multiform)

entries.meaning: Having more than one shape or appearance.
examples: And yet such is the constitution of the human golfing soul that it not only fails to achieve it, but invents for itself multiform and manifold ifs and ans for not achieving it—  […]

entries.meaning: An organism, folktale, etc. that appears in more than one form.
